
RVIAL TO UNION CARBIDE EMERGES IN FRENCH BID
    PARIS, April 3 - {<purchaser>Carburos Metalicos</purchaser>} of Spain has <status>bid</status>
2,205 francs a share for <acqloc>French</acqloc> <acqbus>chemicals</acqbus> group {<acquired>Duffour et
Igon</acquired>}, rivalling the 2,100 franc bid announced yesterday by
Union Carbide France, the French subsidiary of the U.S.
Chemical giant Union Carbide Corp {UK.N}, the stockbrokers'
assocation (CSAC) said here.
    <acqabr>Duffour et Igon</acqabr>'s capital is comprised of 133,100 shares
with a nominal value of 100 francs each. Shares were last
quoted at 856 francs on January 9.
    Banque Paribas will act for <purchabr>Carburos Metalicos</purchabr>, while Union
Carbide France's bid is being led by Rothschild et Associes
Banque.
    <acqabr>Duffour et Igon</acqabr> shares will be suspended on April 6 and 7
and will resume trading on April 8.
